ations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have the shoe strings broken","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to share, to participate with (someone)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become a partner, to be a participant, to be an associate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَرِكَ (šarika) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"polytheism, idolatry","tags":["uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"وَإِذْ قَالَ لُقْمَانُ لِٱبْنِهِ وَهُوَ يَعِظُهُ يَا بُنَيَّ لَا تُشْرِكْ بِٱللّٰهِۖ إِنَّ ٱلشِّرْكَ لَظُلْمٌ عَظِيمٌ","english":"When Luqman said to his son, as he advised him: \"O my son! Do not ascribe any partners to God. Polytheism is indeed a great injustice.\""},{"text":"إِن تَدْعُوهُمْ لَا يَسْمَعُوا دُعَاءَكُمْ وَلَوْ سَمِعُوا مَا ٱسْتَجَابُوا لَكُمْۖ وَيَوْمَ ٱلْقِيَامَةِ يَكْفُرُونَ بِشِرْكِكُمْۚ وَلَا يُنَبِّئُكَ مِثْلُ خَبِيرٍ","english":"If you invoke them they will not hear your invocation, and even if they heard they cannot respond to you, and on the Day of Resurrection they will forswear your polytheism, and none can inform you like the One who is all-aware."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"share","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"net, snare, trap, booby trap"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of شِرَاك (širāk, “shoelace”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of شَرَك (šarak, “net, snare”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"spurious, unsound, phony, false"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"The meaning of associating partners to a god or sharing allegiance across multiple gods is, according to Jeffery 1938, a semantic loan from Old South Arabian 𐩦𐩧𐩫 (s²rk).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null}